</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-34_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Before diving into the intricacies of adult BLS, it's crucial to understand the fundamental terms:
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-36_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Cardiac arrest</strong> - The sudden cessation of heart function, leading to the loss of consciousness and absence of a pulse.













































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Basic Life Support (BLS)</strong> - A set of interventions aimed at sustaining life in individuals experiencing cardiac arrest or respiratory failure until advanced medical help arrives.


























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Chain of survival </strong>- A sequence of actions, including early recognition, prompt activation of emergency services, CPR, defibrillation, and advanced care, designed to improve survival rates in cardiac arrest cases.



























































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-43_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-44_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practice</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-47_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-48_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety (First Aid) Regulations 1981</strong> - Employers are legally obligated to provide adequate first aid provisions in the workplace, including training in BLS for designated first aiders.











































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Resuscitation Council UK Guidelines 2021 </strong>-  The latest guidelines outline the recommended steps for performing high-quality BLS, including the importance of early recognition, effective chest compressions, and prompt defibrillation.























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) Guidelines </strong>- NICE provides evidence-based recommendations for the management of cardiac arrest, emphasising the need for systematic approaches to BLS delivery.























































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-54_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-55_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-56_ pf-heading-1-h3">Early recognition and activation</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-58_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The first step in the chain of survival is recognising the signs of cardiac arrest and activating the emergency response system promptly.

</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-60_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-61_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-62_ pf-heading-1-h3">Effective chest compressions</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-64_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">High-quality chest compressions are the cornerstone of BLS, ensuring the circulation of oxygenated blood to vital organs.


</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-66_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-67_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-68_ pf-heading-1-h3">Airway management and rescue breaths</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-70_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Maintaining a patent airway and delivering rescue breaths can supplement chest compressions, optimising oxygen delivery to the lungs.



</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-72_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-73_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-74_ pf-heading-1-h3">Use of automated external defibrillators (AEDs)</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-76_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">AEDs play a crucial role in the early management of cardiac arrest. They can analyse heart rhythms and deliver shocks if indicated.




</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-78_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hjGZqJ dfjDDX pf-79_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-80_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-82_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-83_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training and certification</strong> - Encourage individuals to undergo certified BLS training courses to equip themselves with the skills and confidence to respond effectively in emergencies.













































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-85_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular skills refresher</strong> - Skills degrade over time, so regular practice and refresher courses are essential to maintaining proficiency in BLS techniques.




























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eWfVMQ iFMXsG pf-87_ pf-text-1"><strong>Community engagement</strong> - Promote community-wide awareness and training initiatives to increase the pool of bystanders capable of performing BLS.




























































